1
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:07,600
[Adapted from Wanzhi's
"Perfect and Casual"]

2
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:10,680
[Perfect and Casual]

3
00:00:11,470 --> 00:00:15,210
[Episode 21]

4
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:31,960
Yun Shu.

5
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,250
Is there something on your mind?

6
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:37,750
No.

7
00:00:37,970 --> 00:00:39,960
Maybe I'm just

8
00:00:40,050 --> 00:00:41,370
a little tired today.

9
00:00:49,150 --> 00:00:50,030
Thank you.

10
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:01,300
I'm going to bed now.

11
00:01:08,929 --> 00:01:09,860
Yun Shu.

12
00:01:17,140 --> 00:01:18,560
Are you not feeling well?

13
00:01:20,990 --> 00:01:21,700
No.

14
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:24,180
Maybe I am just a little sleepy.

15
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:27,910
I'll go back to my room.

16
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:41,460
Mr Zhang.

17
00:01:43,550 --> 00:01:46,340
Did you and Lin Chu Chu

18
00:01:46,670 --> 00:01:47,950
kiss?

19
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:50,510
We did, once.

20
00:01:55,170 --> 00:01:56,310
But last time

21
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:59,150
when I asked if it was your first kiss,

22
00:01:59,790 --> 00:02:01,300
why did you lie to me?

23
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:07,200
Yun Shu.

24
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:14,200
Please let me explain.

25
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:16,660
I'll tell you the situation.

26
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:18,760
I didn't really want to lie to you.

27
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:21,880
The reason why

28
00:02:22,130 --> 00:02:23,920
I didn't tell you the situation

29
00:02:24,650 --> 00:02:25,790
[is because]

30
00:02:26,010 --> 00:02:27,220
[I was abroad at that time.]

31
00:02:27,330 --> 00:02:28,910
[I was informed that my
grandfather was hospitalized]

32
00:02:29,010 --> 00:02:30,610
[and returned at once.]

33
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:31,840
Si Nian.

34
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,040
[Before I left,]

35
00:02:33,510 --> 00:02:34,800
[she kissed me on the cheek.]

36
00:02:34,890 --> 00:02:35,770
What's the matter?

37
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:37,380
[I thought]

38
00:02:37,890 --> 00:02:39,600
[it was a courtesy to say goodbye.]

39
00:02:49,090 --> 00:02:50,190
I see.

40
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,880
Then let's all go to bed early.

41
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:55,750
We're tired today.

42
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:56,720
Okay.

43
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:57,690
Goodnight.

44
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:58,960
Goodnight.

45
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:12,750
Hello, Yi Yi.

46
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:14,290
[Fall in!]

47
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,440
[Fall in now!]

48
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:25,350
[First Prize]

49
00:04:38,090 --> 00:04:39,010
Yun Shu.

50
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:41,460
Mr Zhang.

51
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,120
Well...

52
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:44,400
About what happened last night...

53
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:46,830
Mr Zhang, I'm in a hurry to go out.

54
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,370
I'll talk to you when I get back.

55
00:04:49,390 --> 00:04:50,580
Take care.

56
00:04:50,670 --> 00:04:51,550
Okay.

57
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:53,300
You broke up with each other?

58
00:04:55,009 --> 00:04:55,770
Impossible!

59
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:57,730
Lin dared to break up with you?

60
00:04:58,780 --> 00:04:59,660
Yi Yi.

61
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:02,990
Did you get involved with Gu Xiao again?

62
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:07,380
Yun Shu.

63
00:05:07,460 --> 00:05:09,330
So I'm such a person in your eyes.

64
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:11,690
Do you take my side or not?

65
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,400
Of course I take your side.

66
00:05:14,430 --> 00:05:15,440
So,

67
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:17,480
what on earth happened to you two?

68
00:05:24,610 --> 00:05:25,490
[Gu Xiao]

69
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,460
Why do I keep getting
prank calls recently?

70
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:31,480
It's really annoying.

71
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,630
You're

72
00:05:38,710 --> 00:05:40,220
really boring.

73
00:05:40,310 --> 00:05:41,310
Not fun!

74
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,870
Okay then.

75
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:46,340
How about we play games?

76
00:05:47,810 --> 00:05:48,950
Okay! Play what?

77
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,020
Truth or Dare.

78
00:05:50,110 --> 00:05:51,560
-Okay.
-Let me ask you first.

79
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:52,850
Do you like durian or mango?

80
00:05:52,940 --> 00:05:53,530
Mango.

81
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:54,420
Red or green?

82
00:05:54,509 --> 00:05:54,800
Green.

83
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,180
Leonardo or Lin Nuo?

84
00:05:56,470 --> 00:05:57,270
Leonardo.

85
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,150
Gu Xiao or Lin Nuo?

86
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:59,120
Gu Xiao.

87
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,560
Lin Nuo.

88
00:06:04,770 --> 00:06:06,060
It's just a game.

89
00:06:06,210 --> 00:06:07,460
Don't take it so seriously.

90
00:06:07,690 --> 00:06:09,580
I've always been serious about you.

91
00:06:09,670 --> 00:06:10,810
So have I.

92
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:15,190
The calls are from Gu Xiao, right?

93
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:17,520
Yes.

94
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:18,950
But nothing happened
between us after we broke up.

95
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,110
Lin Nuo, let me explain it.

96
00:06:21,260 --> 00:06:22,480
You don't have to.

97
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,330
That day, Yun Shu asked you
in the dormitory

98
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,730
if you loved Gu Xiao.

99
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:28,080
What was your answer?

100
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:31,580
I haven't thought over at the time.

101
00:06:31,820 --> 00:06:32,850
Actually, I...

102
00:06:32,940 --> 00:06:33,680
Fine.

103
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:35,250
You haven't figured it out, have you?

104
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:36,360
Let me think for you.

105
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,150
What do you want?

106
00:06:38,230 --> 00:06:39,940
You like to play Truth or Dare.

107
00:06:40,660 --> 00:06:42,060
I'll go with Dare.

108
00:06:43,450 --> 00:06:44,470
Let's break up.

109
00:06:51,730 --> 00:06:52,920
Relax, Yi Yi.

110
00:06:53,139 --> 00:06:54,180
Calm down.

111
00:06:54,670 --> 00:06:57,250
After all, you two
have broken up many times.

112
00:06:57,450 --> 00:06:58,440
Yun Shu.

113
00:06:58,530 --> 00:07:00,170
No, I mean

114
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:02,030
it's just an ordinary quarrel
between you two.

115
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:03,480
I'm sure you can make up
in a couple of days.

116
00:07:03,570 --> 00:07:04,750
You did this on purpose today, right?

117
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:06,380
Every word you said is stinging me.

118
00:07:07,090 --> 00:07:07,860
No,

119
00:07:07,940 --> 00:07:09,650
I didn't sleep well last night.

120
00:07:09,740 --> 00:07:11,120
I feel out of it right now.

121
00:07:11,210 --> 00:07:11,750
Hold on.

122
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,160
You haven't slept all night?

123
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:15,270
You usually sleep like a log.

124
00:07:15,390 --> 00:07:16,720
But you didn't last night?

125
00:07:16,810 --> 00:07:17,930
What did you do?

126
00:07:18,810 --> 00:07:19,670
Yi Yi.

127
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,830
Do you remember that I told you before

128
00:07:21,910 --> 00:07:23,540
that Chu Chu had a failed relationship?

129
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:24,730
Her first love

130
00:07:25,470 --> 00:07:26,600
married someone else.

131
00:07:26,690 --> 00:07:27,570
Remember it?

132
00:07:27,890 --> 00:07:28,780
Sure.

133
00:07:28,870 --> 00:07:29,820
You abandoned me

134
00:07:29,910 --> 00:07:31,190
in order to comfort her.

135
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:34,920
Do you know who her first love was?

136
00:07:38,370 --> 00:07:39,560
Mr Zhang.

137
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,780
Mr Zhang?

138
00:07:46,130 --> 00:07:47,250
You and her first love

139
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:48,580
are truly enemies.

140
00:07:48,660 --> 00:07:49,850
It's more than that.

141
00:07:49,940 --> 00:07:51,270
Before Mr Zhang returned,

142
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,210
Chu Chu kissed him.

143
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:55,110
They're both excellent

144
00:07:55,860 --> 00:07:57,350
and perfect.

145
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,130
It's not

146
00:07:59,210 --> 00:08:00,230
an interesting relationship

147
00:08:00,310 --> 00:08:01,720
when the two persons are evenly matched.

148
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:04,050
It's like looking into a mirror
at themselves every morning.

149
00:08:04,140 --> 00:08:05,700
Have you ever seen two identical puzzles

150
00:08:05,790 --> 00:08:07,110
make a complete one?

151
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:10,380
What do you mean?

152
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:11,600
I mean

153
00:08:11,690 --> 00:08:12,660
if Mr Zhang

154
00:08:12,740 --> 00:08:14,230
is really interested in Lin Chu Chu,

155
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:16,150
he wouldn't have married you.

156
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,120
You're dumb.

157
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:21,610
You're right.

158
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:26,420
Yi Yi.

159
00:08:26,690 --> 00:08:28,350
The truth really lies in

160
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:29,510
your hands.

161
00:08:30,130 --> 00:08:30,850
Of course!

162
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:32,300
I'm never wrong about this.

163
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:37,060
Since you are worried,

164
00:08:37,170 --> 00:08:38,900
why not ask Mr Zhang directly?

165
00:08:39,810 --> 00:08:42,230
When I heard about it last night,

166
00:08:42,650 --> 00:08:44,270
I was stunned.

167
00:08:44,590 --> 00:08:45,720
How do you feel now?

168
00:08:45,810 --> 00:08:46,700
Are you "alive" now?

169
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:47,670
Sure.

170
00:08:47,810 --> 00:08:48,980
If you are, ask him now.

171
00:08:49,060 --> 00:08:50,050
Come on.

172
00:08:52,290 --> 00:08:53,980
What about you and Lin Nuo?

173
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:56,400
I think you're right.

174
00:08:56,490 --> 00:08:57,830
I will leave Lin Nuo alone for a few days.

175
00:08:57,940 --> 00:08:59,990
I think he will beg me
to get back together.

176
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,480
And then I'll punish him.

177
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:04,440
We'll punish him.

178
00:09:05,220 --> 00:09:06,370
Send a WeChat message.

179
00:09:10,830 --> 00:09:11,910
What about the data?

180
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:14,210
Take a look, Professor Zhang.

181
00:09:23,490 --> 00:09:25,170
There are still problems with the data.

182
00:09:25,450 --> 00:09:26,340
You're right.

183
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:27,940
I think so, too.

184
00:09:28,190 --> 00:09:29,180
Professor Zhang.

185
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:30,590
Your phone is ringing.

186
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:31,560
Thank you.

187
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:33,650
[Come back early this evening.]

188
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:35,090
[See you at home.]

189
00:09:36,460 --> 00:09:37,390
[Okay]

190
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:41,160
It's Yun Shu, right?

191
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,780
I’ll have dinner with
Meng Ran in the evening.

192
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:46,080
Why don't you bring Yun Shu with you?

193
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,110
Meng Ran?

194
00:09:48,110 --> 00:09:49,900
We were classmates and haven't
seen each other for a long time.

195
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:52,100
-Let's have dinner together.
-Let me ask Yun Shu first.

196
00:09:57,190 --> 00:09:58,820
[Chu Chu and Meng Ran
will have dinner together.]

197
00:09:58,920 --> 00:09:59,500
[She invited us to join.]

198
00:09:59,580 --> 00:10:01,050
She dares to declare war.

199
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:01,870
[Do you want to go?]

200
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,130
Go. You must go.

201
00:10:03,210 --> 00:10:05,080
No. It will be three of us.

202
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:06,150
I'll do it.

203
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:07,490
[Okay, honey.]

204
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:08,780
[Send me the address.]

205
00:10:19,930 --> 00:10:21,250
Is this the shop

206
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:22,800
where Chu Chu bought clothes?

207
00:10:23,020 --> 00:10:23,730
Yes.

208
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:25,580
Who says only Lin Chu Chu can wear this.

209
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:53,240
Do I not look good?

210
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:56,380
No.

211
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:57,420
You're very beautiful.

212
00:10:57,510 --> 00:10:58,810
It suits you well.

213
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,150
Sorry, I'm late.

214
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,440
Where are the two?

215
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:04,960
They have already gone upstairs.

216
00:11:05,110 --> 00:11:06,210
Let's go too.

217
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:07,180
Okay.

218
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:11,230
Yun Shu, here you are.

219
00:11:11,310 --> 00:11:12,640
Sorry, I'm late.

220
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,670
Mr Meng, Chu Chu.

221
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:22,130
What a coincidence.

222
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:25,870
You look pretty.

223
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:26,820
All right.

224
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:27,790
Take a seat.

225
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:28,910
Okay.

226
00:11:34,310 --> 00:11:35,000
Waiter.

227
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,380
We're ready to order.

228
00:11:36,470 --> 00:11:37,350
Okay.

229
00:11:40,110 --> 00:11:41,560
Who would like to order, please?

230
00:11:44,470 --> 00:11:45,150
Chu Chu.

231
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:47,990
You just returned from abroad, so
you can order whatever you want to eat.

232
00:11:48,890 --> 00:11:49,980
I just came back.

233
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:51,640
I don't know what's tasty.

234
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,540
Let Yun Shu order.

235
00:11:56,510 --> 00:11:57,900
Let Chu Chu order.

236
00:11:57,990 --> 00:11:59,380
I'm not very good at ordering.

237
00:12:02,010 --> 00:12:03,160
Let Si Nian order.

238
00:12:08,430 --> 00:12:09,820
See what you want to eat.

239
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:10,790
Pick anything.

240
00:12:13,290 --> 00:12:15,460
We want a Lily-Flavoured
Stewed Angelica Soup.

241
00:12:15,620 --> 00:12:16,500
Okay.

242
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,960
Si Nian, aren't you allergic to lilies?

243
00:12:22,730 --> 00:12:23,600
Then I'll change it.

244
00:12:23,690 --> 00:12:24,430
That's okay.

245
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:26,060
Help yourself to whatever you want.

246
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:33,560
Then,

247
00:12:33,730 --> 00:12:36,060
we want a Pan-Seared Green Chili Pepper.

248
00:12:36,140 --> 00:12:37,750
Everyone can eat spicy food, right?

249
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,350
Sure.

250
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,320
Serve one.

251
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:40,840
Okay.

252
00:12:41,340 --> 00:12:42,340
I can,

253
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:45,220
but Si Nian doesn't eat spicy food.

254
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:52,180
You didn't tell me.

255
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:54,130
When we prepared

256
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:55,240
spicy dishes,

257
00:12:55,490 --> 00:12:56,650
you ate it too.

258
00:12:56,730 --> 00:12:58,290
I used to not eat too much,

259
00:12:58,650 --> 00:12:59,810
but I can now.

260
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,860
Pick whatever you like.

261
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,430
How about I order?

262
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:09,860
Yun Shu, let me order.

263
00:13:10,070 --> 00:13:11,200
What's delicious here?

264
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:12,020
We have a lot.

265
00:13:12,110 --> 00:13:13,380
We can serve every dish on the menu.

266
00:13:13,470 --> 00:13:15,010
Tell me what you want to eat.

267
00:13:20,810 --> 00:13:21,940
And

268
00:13:22,060 --> 00:13:23,260
one more...

269
00:13:25,330 --> 00:13:26,590
What do you want to eat?

270
00:13:31,410 --> 00:13:32,620
Tell me.
Let me order it for you.

271
00:13:32,740 --> 00:13:33,550
Pork Ribs.

272
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:34,520
Pork Ribs.

273
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:35,630
Okay.

274
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:36,600
Okay, Pork Ribs.

275
00:13:37,090 --> 00:13:37,970
Okay.

276
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,260
Chu Chu.

277
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:41,470
What do you want to eat?

278
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:42,810
Squirrel-Shaped Mandarin Fish.

279
00:13:42,930 --> 00:13:43,650
-Do you have it?
-Yes.

280
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:44,610
-One, please.
-Okay.

281
00:13:44,690 --> 00:13:45,570
What else?

282
00:13:45,860 --> 00:13:46,850
A portion of.

283
00:13:46,940 --> 00:13:47,650
Pork Ribs please.

284
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:48,620
Thank you.

285
00:13:53,220 --> 00:13:53,980
Chu Chu likes spicy food.

286
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:55,150
One more.

287
00:13:55,580 --> 00:13:56,990
Diced Chicken with Chili Pepper.

288
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:17,680
We're leaving.

289
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:36,340
Do you also like Yun Shu?

290
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,020
I like you, too.

291
00:14:42,110 --> 00:14:43,310
